snippet.textDisplay: Once upon a time there happened to be a show called Coke Studio which was famous for its melody, soothing music arrangement and great singing talent picked up according to songs and lyrics. Then its producer Rohail Hayyat left the show and within three years there are just ruins of that great show where every wanna-be great music director is competing in a senseless noise making competition. And if you don't agree just check how Rohail had used same singer (Haroon) with Sanam Marvi in ''Koi Labda" ... here it is just noiseeeeeeeee...................!!!!!! So Disappointed. No blame on singers they are all very talented but it is music of CS which has lost in this noise.
